title: For Sale:  18" AR-15, Battlecomp, PSA, Magpul, Troy VTAC // $1,050 OBO
postcontent:
Bills are forcing me to sell my ultra-soft shooting and flawlessly reliable 18" AR-15. What makes it recoilless is the rifle-length gas system combined with the battlecomp 1.0 muzzle device. With this setup you can actually get the gun recoiling DOWN if you shoot fast enough.

It is immensely controllable and has been put to good use, surviving a training class flawlessly without a single stoppage for any reason.

The rifle's Palmetto State Armory lower is built with a White Oak Armament lower parts kit and includes their ALG trigger. The stock is a Magpul ACS, grip and trigger guard are also Magpul. The barrel is a Green Mountain 18" made of 416R stainless steel and has a 1:7 twist (Green Mountain namelessly makes the barrels used in many top quality AR makers), with a Wilson Combat low-profile gas block. It runs an Alpha Omega Weaponry M16 BCG and the long handguard is a Troy VTAC.

It also comes with ARMS 40L backup flipup sights already installed and zeroed for 50 yards.

As you can see (or Google), the parts are all top-shelf and it shows. It shoots like a dream and the weight distribution makes it incredibly maneuverable. There is some wear on the left side of the lower from my belt buckle as it swung on me while slung, and there is some scratching on the bottom of the handguard from resting on different real-life barricades like car hoods and boulders. Obviously none of these minor cosmetic blemishes will impede function in any way and if I had planned on selling it then I would've taken better care of its aesthetics. I meant to keep this as my One Rifle but real life has intervened as it always does.

I will also include two metal high-quality D&H 30-round magazines with the rifle.

Price is $1,050 or best offer; cash only, no trades. I don't think you'll ever find this nice of a rifle at this low of a price on Armslist ever again.

postcontent: This is a Nagoya Arsenal T II paratrooper that bubba, unfortunately, decided to do a little work on.  I picked it up several years ago with the intent of a restoration...but have lost the interest and don't have the time.  It has a full and untouched mum.  The cleaning rod is missing.  There are a couple buggered screws around the mounting plates but the metal is otherwise in very good shape.  Bore is excellent and I fired a few rounds years ago and found it to be a good shooter.  Bubba did a job on the wood finish...it has been lightly sanded and refinished to an orange like color...much darker than the original finish.  Matching numbers on the bolt, safety, firing pin, extractor, receiver and front bayonet lug. Front half assembly number of 271 matches the rear mounting plate number and the number on the takedown lug.  Front assembly plate number is 916. This is as close to fully matching as u will get I think.  It was common for the plates to be mismatched during assembly I believe.  There is a little wiggle when the 2 halves are assembled...the detent pin seems to be pushed in a little...may have a weak or missing spring there.  It is not crushed..but moves freely and is flush with the mounting plate.  This is a quite valuable rifle in good condition...understand that there is work to be done here.  I am throwing out a price and will consider cash offers.  I will consider partial trade on any Model Glock 9MM that is in good shape and complete. postcontent:
Aimpoint CompM4 M68 CCO 
Aimpoint CompM4 sights are the finest sights that Aimpoint has ever produced. The improved energy efficiency provides up to 8 years of continuous use from a single AA battery! Aimpoint CompM4 sights incorporate an integral mount that eliminates the need for a separate ring and can be customized with vertical and forward spacers to fit a variety of firearms. They can also be used by hunters and sport shooters that need night vision compatibility. CompM4 sights are available in two versions. The two versions are identical except that the CompM4 offers a high battery compartment, while the CompM4S offers a low battery compartment. The Aimpoint CompM4 is now the latest version of the US Army's M68 CCO (Close-Combat Optic), continuing a legacy that Aimpoint has maintained since 1997. The performance of the CompM4 sights is optimized for use with all generations of Night Vision Devices (NVDs), but is especially suited for 3rd generation night vision technology. Aimpoint's unique band-pass coating on the front lens reflects select frequencies of red light at near 100% efficiency in order to give the highest possible dot brightness with the smallest amount of energy while transmitting nearly 100% of light in the Infrared and near-infrared part of the spectrum to provide the clearest, brightest image possible when used with a 3rd generation NVD. With 7 NVD-compatible brightness settings and 9 Daylight settings including one extra-bright setting, the CompM4 and CompM4S are ready for use around the clock.
